=== BagavadgItAyAM 6.30 ===

--- line ---
yu[He who]->yo mA[me]->mAm=>mAM paSyati[sees] sarvatra[everywhere]
"He who sees me everywhere"

sarva[all things]->sarvam=>sarvaM ca[and] mayI[in me]->mayi paSyati[sees] .
"and sees all things in me,"

--- line ---
tasya[to him]+aham[I]=tasyAham=>tasyAhaM na[not] praRaSyAmi[am][lost]
"to him, I am not lost"

sa[he] ca[and] me[to me] na[not] praRaSyati[is][lost] ..
"and he is not lost to me."
